column1: Long-Term Trend Mathematics, Age 9, Region of the country
Average scale scores for age 9 long-term trend mathematics, by region of the country [CENSREG] and jurisdiction: 2022, 2020, 2012, 2008, 2004, 1999, 1996, 1994, 1992, 1990, 1986, 1982, and 1978
NOTE: Some apparent differences between estimates may not be statistically significant.

SOURCE: U.S. Department of Education, Institute of Education Sciences, National Center for Education Statistics, National Assessment of Educational Progress (NAEP), 1978, 1982, 1986, 1990, 1992, 1994, 1996, 1999, 2004, 2008, 2012, 2020, and 2022 Long-Term Trend Mathematics Assessments.
